The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | CSA president steps down
                                                                                                                                                                                                     CSA president steps down
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Cricket South Africa (CSA) president Norman Arendse handed in a shock resignation on Wednesday, citing differences between himself and CSA chief executive Gerald Majola. Arendses resignationwas with immediate effect.         
	In a statement issued on Wednesday, Majola expressed surprise at the sudden turn of events. He said, It is with surprise and regret that I received the news of Norman Arendses resignation as president of Cricket South Africa.         
	Majola added, It is also with surprise and regret that I have learnt that he has cited irretrievable differences between us as one of the reasons for his resignation.         
	The CEO stressed that CSA will now work towards strengthening the countrys cricket.                                                                                                                          
